      <processinfo id="aspace_f98d812696ca056de1398a685cfe1644">
         <head>Processing Information</head>
         <p>The collection received preliminary processing around the time of acquisition in 1978. During reprocessing of the collection in 2011, writings and other materials were established as separate series and arranged alphabetically by title and material type respectively.</p>
         <p>Formerly classed as Za Powel.</p>  
      </processinfo>
      <bioghist id="aspace_65b7c1d988b5b5a002a8b8d226974932">
         <head>Robert J. Hare Powel</head>
         <p>Robert J. Hare Powel, graduate of the Yale School of Drama (1930) and playwright.</p>  
      </bioghist>
      <scopecontent id="aspace_2282ea69a1b68782c05adba143092ff2">
         <head>Scope and Contents</head>
         <p>The collection contains writings and other material documenting the early career of playwright Robert J. Hare Powel. Writings include scenarios, outlines, and drafts for scripts of stage plays, most of which appear to date from the late-1920s to mid-1930s. Other materials include correspondence, photographs, and a scrapbook documenting Powel's work and theater generally. Correspondence consists of letters to Powel and comments regarding productions of his plays. Photographs consist of stage shots of Yale productions and cartes de visite of actors. The scrapbook contains clippings, printed ephemera, such as theater programs, and photographs.</p>  
      </scopecontent>
      <arrangement id="aspace_727dc41bbdea0a93587b92548ae9d5ab">
         <head>Arrangement</head>
         <p>Organized into two series: I. Writings, 1928-1957. II. Other Material, 1869-1959.</p>  
      </arrangement>
